1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:04,390
Episode 14

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:13,420
Oh, you are awake? Shall I help you?

3
00:00:13,420 --> 00:00:17,720
Then come over here and press it down.

4
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:22,160
- I can just press it down?
- Yes.

5
00:00:23,810 --> 00:00:27,190
Woah, this is hard.

6
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:31,770
You need to do it harder.  Are you going to pull the noodles that way?

7
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:41,890
Wow, this is so amazing.

8
00:00:41,890 --> 00:00:45,840
There are many amazing things.

9
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:49,700
This is hard. You do it every day?

10
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:57,070
Of course. You think I miss a day? I've been doing this for 47 years.

11
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:11,360
Hey go-fer.

12
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:16,910
- Do you think living is enjoyable?
- What?

13
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:21,300
When I look at your face, I must ask.

14
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:24,000
"I can't die.  I've run away from Seoul." and

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,470
it's written on your forehead.

16
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:33,900
As you live, something will always happen.

17
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:37,930
You aren't the only one. It happens to everyone.

18
00:01:37,930 --> 00:01:43,370
And everytime something hits you, what's the use of tucking in your tail and running away?

19
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:49,480
Just grab him by the collar, pull and twist his hair,

20
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:52,210
and get him in the groin!

21
00:01:52,210 --> 00:01:55,540
If you fall to the ground, be resolved to get back,

22
00:01:55,540 --> 00:02:00,060
you have to fight until you pop a vein.

23
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:03,200
There's no other way.

24
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:08,140
That's how you can smile later. Alright?

25
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:13,440
I am  an ignorant old lady  who fills people's bellies.

26
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:19,270
But what are you guys?  Aren't you supposed to be filling souls or something?

27
00:02:19,270 --> 00:02:22,280
So you shouldn't be unhappy.

28
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:26,020
It makes other people unhappy.

29
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:31,540
Smile a bit, smile!

30
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:36,480
You can smile if you are rolling in shit! Who the hell are you?

31
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,400
Smile!

32
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:11,800
Conductor. Thank you for taking me yesterday.

33
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:16,720
I should be thankful. I would've been hit if it weren't for you.

34
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:20,260
I can contact your grandma from time to time, can't I?

35
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:24,270
Didn't you get each other's numbers? Just don't pull me into it.

36
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:28,150
- I'm going.
- Bye!

37
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:39,370
You seem to be in a good mood. Smiling and everything.

38
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:46,300
I've decided that I'm not going to cry anymore.

39
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:55,340
You didn't pick up your phone yesterday. Did you go somewhere? You seemed to be out all night.

40
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:57,680
Why do you want to know?

41
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:02,170
I don't know, either. My sick girlfriend called a friend before me.

42
00:04:02,170 --> 00:04:05,850
Say it correctly. I am not your girlfriend.

43
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:12,400
You know you are my dead brother's girlfriend.

44
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,750
- Do you really have to talk that way?
- I'm not wrong though, so what?

45
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:17,320
It's not right. You have no evidence!

46
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,870
I told you there is.
Come anytime. I'll show you.

47
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:23,700
Instead of running away in front of me as though you are looking at another guy.

48
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:31,700
I'm not going to run away. Show it to me, I will look at it.

49
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:48,830
- What are you doing?
- This is how I feel right now.

50
00:04:51,890 --> 00:04:56,450
Did you stay at my house last night? Why are you staying at  someone else's house?

51
00:04:57,420 --> 00:05:02,340
Some one else's house? Do you really know no other way to talk?

52
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:06,960
You have no idea how I felt yesterday.

53
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:14,630
You were with Hong Yi Yeong the whole time, weren't you? I didn't want to know but I found out.

54
00:05:14,630 --> 00:05:19,230
There are dozens of people who saw the great man picking her up.

55
00:05:20,550 --> 00:05:23,840
Did you two sleep together?

56
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:30,540
Do I need to answer you?

57
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:33,700
Shall I give you some advice?

58
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:37,350
If you take her side, only she will be ruined.

59
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:40,920
That's what the world we live in looks like!

60
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:44,550
Even now, she's walking a fine line.  How long do you think she will last?

61
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:47,890
If you aren't going to take responsibility all the way, then you need to back off.

62
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:50,660
Before I ruin her.

63
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:55,780
I neither took her side nor slept with her. That's not our relationship.

64
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:58,600
She looked like she was having a hard time yesterday so I took her for some fresh air.

65
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:03,710
I also was having a hard time. I was having a horrible time.

66
00:06:03,710 --> 00:06:07,530
You should know as well.

67
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:11,430
I feel like I'm continuing to roll in disgusting mud.

68
00:06:12,730 --> 00:06:16,180
That's how I was yesterday.

69
00:06:17,330 --> 00:06:21,120
I wanted to be comforted, too.

70
00:06:22,810 --> 00:06:29,170
I'm not a robot, I'm a human being. I also get hurt and scarred also.

71
00:06:29,170 --> 00:06:37,380
If the guy I like sleeps with someone else, then it makes me feel I want to die.

72
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:31,180
All the places you took me are in these pictures.

73
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:35,610
To where Kim Ian took me.

74
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,060
Yes...

75
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:52,650
Show me the knife. You have it, don't you?

76
00:07:52,650 --> 00:07:55,840
I'll remember if I see it.

77
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:23,420
Who are you? Who... who are you?!

78
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:27,290
Don't come near me!

79
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:35,940
What's wrong?

80
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:47,080
Nothing. I'm sorry but I'm going to get going now.

81
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:53,150
You came?

82
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,540
- Your cast is off.
- Yes.

83
00:09:57,540 --> 00:10:00,740
It feels as refreshing as if I drank a million Sprites.

84
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:03,530
What's going on?

85
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:10,620
I have something that I wanted to ask you.

86
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:14,710
I'm on my way back from meeting Jang Yun.

87
00:10:14,710 --> 00:10:16,730
Why were you with him again?

88
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:26,070
That person said... that maybe I could've killed his brother.

89
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:28,520
Did he say that to you?

90
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:32,650
Saying that you killed his brother?

91
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:42,290
Eonni, you knew already, didn't you?

92
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:49,580
That I didn't ride in a taxi but that I rode in Kim Ian's car?

93
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:56,420
Why didn't you tell me the truth? Was there a reason?

94
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:59,850
What reason? You've never ridden in Kim Ian's car.

95
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:01,600
And aunt and uncle both know too?

96
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:05,510
What would Mom and Dad know?  What did you hear from that guy?

97
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:11,690
He said that on Kim Ian's body there was a stab wound.

98
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:18,120
He even showed me the knife.

99
00:11:19,590 --> 00:11:23,360
Knife? What kind of knife?

100
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:28,450
The one that comes out a lot in movies. A switchblade knife.

101
00:11:28,450 --> 00:11:30,450
But...

102
00:11:32,310 --> 00:11:35,560
there was also blood on my hands.

103
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:39,890
Knife? What kind of knife?

104
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:44,590
It's the knife that he found in the place where I was found.

105
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:50,540
He thinks that I stabbed and killed him with that knife.

106
00:11:50,540 --> 00:11:52,190
He really is crazy, isn't he?

107
00:11:52,190 --> 00:11:54,520
How can he make an innocent person into a murder suspect?

108
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,170
Get up. Let's go meet him.

109
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:58,470
Get up right now!

110
00:11:58,470 --> 00:12:00,630
But...

111
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:05,290
what he says...

112
00:12:07,110 --> 00:12:10,390
I think it's right.

113
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:15,180
You... do you know what that means?

114
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:20,350
Look at me. Look right at me. Get yourself together, Yi Yeong.

115
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:23,030
Don't believe a single word that bastard said. It's all a lie.

116
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:26,350
They're all things that he imagined in his head.

117
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:30,840
You didn't kill him. You found the knife and you found it at a different location.

118
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:34,740
There is not a single bit of evidence that you rode in the same car as him.

119
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:37,410
They said that my purse...

120
00:12:39,420 --> 00:12:41,260
was found in Kim Ian's car.

121
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,820
Who says that? He does?

122
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:45,480
How can you believe him?!

123
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:49,720
I'm the one who met with the police right after you were found!

124
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:52,460
You... Don't meet that man anymore.

125
00:12:52,460 --> 00:12:55,810
He is  intimidating you. Do you understand.

126
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:59,660
Answer me!

127
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,450
Okay.

128
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:26,700
Where are you?

129
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,690
We are all meeting in order to prepare for Wang Su Seok's birthday.

130
00:13:29,690 --> 00:13:31,990
Hurry up and get over here.

131
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:52,340
What are you, a gangster or something?

132
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:55,440
What did you say to the trash among your acquaintances?

133
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,570
Tell me right now.

134
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:59,390
It's exactly as you said.

135
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:05,030
You got the Guadagnini from my dad.  You said it with your own mouth.

136
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,710
Are you that stupid?

137
00:14:07,710 --> 00:14:13,470
Why? Do you regret making fun with your own mouth because you hear the sound of your bank account being robbed?

138
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:18,490
You were giving lessons although you didn't want to, because you wanted a professor position, didn't you?

139
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:20,930
Wake up, Ha Eun Ju.

140
00:14:20,930 --> 00:14:23,410
A professor at Sinyeong College?

141
00:14:25,810 --> 00:14:27,760
Not anyone can do that.

142
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:31,080
No matter how much you struggle, you'll never be able to enter my lane.

143
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:36,400
We, whom you treated like trash, were bestowing kindness on you all this time.

144
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:39,930
You didn't even recognize that kindness that let you earn a living.

145
00:14:39,930 --> 00:14:42,160
You little—

146
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:46,120
Does it hurt?

147
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:49,580
What are you going to do?  If you can't play your instrument, how are you going to make a living?

148
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,240
Let go of me.

149
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:51,920
You aren't letting me go?

150
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:53,630
Yes, that's right.

151
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:57,040
Ha Eun Ju, you are done for!

152
00:14:57,040 --> 00:15:00,470
We are done in just one stroke.

153
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:08,610
Should we make a bet on who will finish it first?

154
00:15:08,610 --> 00:15:11,810
You're dead, Choi Seo Ju.

155
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:20,360
We'll see who's done for, soon enough.

156
00:16:00,590 --> 00:16:03,180
I made coffee without your permission.

157
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:07,070
The coffee is very delicious, Conductor.

158
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:12,040
Get out of my room. You shouldn't be here.

159
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:14,100
I'm a bit disappointed.

160
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:17,980
I always thought of you as my little brother.

161
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:20,840
You've been through a lot. Since a year ago.

162
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,880
Am I wrong?

163
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:26,810
What is the reason for you coming here?

164
00:16:26,810 --> 00:16:30,030
Didn't you receive everything that was promised to you?

165
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:32,310
I haven't received it all yet.

166
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:34,940
We haven't found the lost object yet.

167
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:40,290
That bastard Professor Kang said that I have to find it in order to get the rest of the money.

168
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:44,280
Anyway, all the geek bastards are trash.

169
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:46,560
You are also trash.

170
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:50,070
Get out of my office right now.

171
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:51,790
Aigoo.

172
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:55,660
Am I dirty or something?

173
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:58,120
That's your fault.

174
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:01,620
You people sent me to jail.

175
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:06,290
Conductor, do you know what it's like in jail?

176
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:11,020
I'll give you money, so will you go to jail in my place?

177
00:17:12,130 --> 00:17:18,470
When I got back from that hell, you were all living well.

178
00:17:18,470 --> 00:17:25,400
As if what happened one year ago never even happened.  You're laughing, smiling, and dating.

179
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:28,530
You and that bastard Professor Kang.

180
00:17:28,530 --> 00:17:30,620
Even that girl Hong Yi Yeong.

181
00:17:30,620 --> 00:17:33,150
I'm going to get revenge on all of you.

182
00:17:33,150 --> 00:17:38,960
Since the person at the very bottom of the pyramid lives the life of an insect anyway.

183
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:44,400
You... are you threatening me right now?

184
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,370
It's not a threat, Conductor.

185
00:17:48,690 --> 00:17:51,550
I'm asking you a favor.

186
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:55,730
You... know what Hong Yi Yeong possesses, right?

187
00:17:55,730 --> 00:17:57,650
You should find it also.

188
00:17:57,650 --> 00:18:00,660
You have to find it, so that I can get the rest of my money.

189
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:04,840
Then... I will forgive you.

190
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:08,830
If you've said everything you wanted to, then leave.  Don't come back here, I'm warning you.

191
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:11,690
Whether I come or not, that's up to me.

192
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:14,070
Thank you for the coffee.

193
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:06,820
♫ Happy birthday to you

194
00:19:06,820 --> 00:19:09,820
♫ Happy birthday to you

195
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:12,740
♫ Our beloved Unni Wang

196
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:16,330
♫ Happy birthday to you

197
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:28,800
First Oboist.

198
00:19:29,860 --> 00:19:31,090
Happy birthday.

199
00:19:31,090 --> 00:19:32,870
Thank you.

200
00:19:33,730 --> 00:19:35,030
First Oboist!

201
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:37,700
-- We love you!

202
00:19:41,170 --> 00:19:42,850
Thank you all.

203
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:46,910
I can't believe that it's been 10 years since I entered Sinyeong Philharmonic.

204
00:19:46,910 --> 00:19:48,910
Drink as much as you want today.

205
00:19:48,910 --> 00:19:53,330
I will be paying for all the drinks today!

206
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:09,900
I shoud forget you.

207
00:20:32,370 --> 00:20:34,770
Why did you come here?

208
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:37,040
You don't often come to these kinds of places.

209
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:41,160
It's because I want to stay next to you. What about it?

210
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:42,690
It's not like you're keeping tabs on a suspect.

211
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:57,040
Encore, encore, encore!

212
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,790
Encore, encore!

213
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:02,370
I can't. I'm so tired.

214
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:06,930
Over there, our troublemaker Hong Yi Yeong,

215
00:21:06,930 --> 00:21:10,330
Come out here and sing a song!

216
00:21:11,310 --> 00:21:14,460
Hong Yi Yeong!  Hong Yi Yeong!

217
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:16,660
Hong Yi Yeong!

218
00:21:16,660 --> 00:21:21,390
I'm not a member of the orchestra now.

219
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:24,450
I'll go out!

220
00:21:28,230 --> 00:21:31,060
TT written by Black Eyed Pilseung 2

221
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:43,770
♫ I can't do this,

222
00:21:43,770 --> 00:21:45,680
♫ I can't do that.

223
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:49,200
♫ While I just look at it  Ba-ba-ba-baby.

224
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:53,480
♫ I only imagive every day together with a name. I'm sorry Baby.

225
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:56,190
♫ We don't know each other yet.

226
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,700
♫ I'm like T T, whoo! ♫
("TT” is similar to the korean vowel ㅠ, the crying emoticon)

227
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:59,790
♫ Just like T T, whoo! ♫

228
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:03,160
♫ You don't know how I feel.  It's too much!  It's too much! ♫

229
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,030
♫ Just like T T, whoo! ♫

230
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:07,300
♫ just like TT (oh whoa) ♫

231
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:11,570
♫ Tell me that you’d be my baby ♫

232
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:15,520
Thank you. Thank you.

233
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:19,510
Okay, the next person is...

234
00:22:19,510 --> 00:22:22,240
The one drinking by himself.

235
00:22:22,240 --> 00:22:25,150
Our guest!

236
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:32,340
Our genius guest pianist, Jang Yoon.

237
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:35,610
Sing!

238
00:22:48,230 --> 00:22:53,850
♫ It's been a while.

239
00:22:53,850 --> 00:23:02,140
♫ As much as I'm ashamed to say this

240
00:23:02,140 --> 00:23:05,670
♫ Just looking at you

241
00:23:05,670 --> 00:23:09,250
♫ Like a friend who already knows everything

242
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:14,430
♫ We must have always been together ♫

243
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:23,790
♫ When you're tired or sad ♫

244
00:23:23,790 --> 00:23:27,420
♫  Both when you're lonely♫

245
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:30,260
♫  and because you're suffering apart♫

246
00:23:30,260 --> 00:23:37,230
♫ you are hurting, I will wipe away your tears ♫

247
00:23:37,230 --> 00:23:40,990
♫ There is a man. ♫

248
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:44,570
♫ Who loved you so much ♫

249
00:23:44,570 --> 00:23:48,110
♫ There is a man  ♫

250
00:23:48,110 --> 00:23:52,570
